    "description": "Join the Navkar Corporation Asia Pacific Associates family as a Supply Chain Manager in Kochi. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout Navkar Corporation Asia Pacific Associates:\nNavkar Corporation Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Handle customs clearance for import and export shipments\n• Manage relationships with third-party logistics providers\n• Implement cost-saving initiatives in transportation and warehousing\n• Ensure proper handling, packaging, and labeling of goods\n• Prepare MIS reports on delivery performance and SLA adherence\n• Coordinate with customer service teams to resolve delivery issues\n• Coordinate with warehousing teams for inbound and outbound operations\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in INCOTERMS\n• Proficiency in Reverse Logistics\n• Proficiency in Fleet Management\n• Proficiency in Vendor Management\n• Proficiency in GPS Tracking Systems\n• Proficiency in Customs Clearance\n• Proficiency in Inventory Management\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Flexible working hours\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Kochi, Kerala, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Navkar Corporation Asia Pacific Associates!",
